cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.SE

This paper deals with the security of the Domain Name System (DNS), which is a critical component of network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network analysis and detection techniques, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of DNS servers, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper presents a system that was developed to validate the proposed technique, which could be classified under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
